    "source_sections": {
      "references": "[FaMc93] Faudree, R. J. and McKay, B., A conjecture of Erd\\H{o}s and the Ramsey number $r(W_6)$. J. Combinatorial Math. and Combinatorial Computing (1993), 23-31.",
      "remarks": "Erd\\H{o}s originally conjectured that $R(G)\\geq R(k)$, which is trivial for $k=3$, but fails already for $k=4$, as Faudree and McKay \\cite{FaMc93} showed that $R(W)=17$ for the pentagonal wheel $W$.\n\nSince $R(k)\\leq 4^k$ this is trivial for $\\epsilon\\geq 3/4$. Yuval Wigderson points out that $R(G)\\gg 2^{k/2}$ for any $G$ with chromatic number $k$ (via a random colouring), which asymptotically matches the best-known lower bounds for $R(k)$.\n\nThis problem is #12 and #13 in Ramsey Theory in the graphs problem collection."
    },
